projectInfo.name: Missing Maps - Ambodivoahangy, Madagascar - Réduction des risques de catastrophe (Manaratsandry)
projectInfo.shortDescription:
The Betsiboka River, which runs through 3 districts in the Boeny region, is one of the largest rivers in Madagascar. The insufficiency of effective actions to manage this basin causes consequent and recurring floods in this area, after the  a cyclone or  during heavy rains.
The actions of Handicap International project aim to reduce the risk of disasters by preparing the most vulnerable populations. In this context, CartONG supports Handicap International for the mapping of the area, which will then be used by HI teams to plan their operations.

projectInfo.instructions:
1. Imagery details
=======
The mapping will be done using Bing imagery 


2. Buildings
=======

Please map all of the building using the tags below:
* In the ID editor: label the area as “Building” then correct for right angles with the “S” key

* In JOSM: from the Tags/Memberships window, click “Add” and use the tag *building=yes*; then correct for right angles using the “Q” key 
* Or using plugin building in JOSM

3. Roads and Paths
